introduced us to his friend

1531
01:22:13.680 --> 01:22:16.035
who owned a boxing and storage company
out of Tirana.

1532
01:22:16.600 --> 01:22:19.034
This is Enver. I grew up with him.

1533
01:22:19.280 --> 01:22:20.280
Nice to meet you. Enver.

1534
01:22:20.480 --> 01:22:24.189
You too. Bashkim told me
a little about your situation.

1535
01:22:24.400 --> 01:22:27.039
Yeah. look. to put it simply.
we have a weight problem.

1536
01:22:27.240 --> 01:22:29.196
We're shipping
a large quantity of ammunition

1537
01:22:29.400 --> 01:22:31.118
from Albania to Afghanistan.

1538
01:22:31.320 --> 01:22:32.760
Right now. it's packed in heavy tins

1539
01:22:32.960 --> 01:22:34.154
inside big wooden crates.

1540
01:22:34.360 --> 01:22:35.554
And what we would like to do

1541
01:22:35.800 --> 01:22:37.600
is to transfer those bullets
into plastic bags

1542
01:22:37.800 --> 01:22:39.240
and then put those in double-walled.

1543
01:22:39.400 --> 01:22:40.753
corrugated fiberboard boxes.

1544
01:22:42.840 --> 01:22:43.920
Do you know what those are?

1545
01:22:44.320 --> 01:22:46.515
Yeah. of course. For what reason?

1546
01:22:46.960 --> 01:22:47.960
We just told you.

1547
01:22:48.200 --> 01:22:49.720
What the fuck is it with this country?

1548
01:22:50.960 --> 01:22:54.635
The original packaging. it's too heavy.

1549
01:22:55.120 --> 01:22:57.680
Too many crates. We need to streamline.

1550
01:22:58.360 --> 01:23:00.237
Okay. How many crates?

1551
01:23:00.440 --> 01:23:03.398
A lot. It's 100 million
rounds of ammunition.

1552
01:23:03.600 --> 01:23:08.071
Understood. But how many actual crates?

1553
01:23:09.880 --> 01:23:13.316
We have 68.520 crates.

1554
01:23:15.000 --> 01:23:16.274
I've seen it.

1555
01:23:16.480 --> 01:23:18.152
It's fucking crazy.

1556
01:23:43.960 --> 01:23:44.960
Done.

1557
01:23:57.600 --> 01:23:59.989
So 50 men. eight weeks.

1558
01:24:00.360 --> 01:24:04.433
I can do it for $100.000.

1559
01:24:05.720 --> 01:24:07.597
100.000 U.S. dollars?

1560
01:24:07.960 --> 01:24:08.960
Yeah.

1561
01:24:09.480 --> 01:24:12.313
- Give us a second.
- Yeah. One second. please.

1562
01:24:13.400 --> 01:24:16.358
Okay. I'm going to talk very seriously.

1563
01:24:16.840 --> 01:24:18.120
DAVID: It was hard not to laugh.

1564
01:24:18.280 --> 01:24:21.192
I mean. not only was this guy
saving the entire deal.

1565
01:24:21.400 --> 01:24:22.913
but by repacking all the ammo

1566
01:24:23.160 --> 01:24:26.516
we would increase our profit margin
by almost $3 million.

1567
01:24:26.920 --> 01:24:28.320
Where should we get dinner tonight?

1568
01:24:28.560 --> 01:24:30.710
There's this place by the hotel.
It's pretty good.

1569
01:24:30.960 --> 01:24:33.110
Okay. All right. go ahead.

1570
01:24:33.440 --> 01:24:34.589
Okay. deal.

1571
01:24:41.280 --> 01:24:43.111
It was even better than we thought.

1572
01:24:43.400 --> 01:24:46.676
We were trading heavy wooden crates
for light cardboard boxes.

1573
01:24:46.880 --> 01:24:49.633
Eight ounce tins for plastic bags.

1574
01:24:50.720 --> 01:24:52.073
By repacking the ammo.

1575
01:24:52.280 --> 01:24:54.874
we would lighten our overall load
by 180 tons.

1576
01:24:56.920 --> 01:24:59.275
180 fucking tons!

1577
01:24:59.480 --> 01:25:03.155
That meant fewer flights
using lighter planes burning less fuel.

1578
01:25:04.720 --> 01:25:07.871
Which all added up to more money for us.

1579
01:25:12.640 --> 01:25:14.915
On December 8th. 2007.

1580
01:25:15.120 --> 01:25:17.350
AEY delivered the first 5 million rounds

1581
01:25:17.560 --> 01:25:19.551
to the Afghan army.

1582
01:25:21.520 --> 01:25:23.397
It went off without a hitch.

1583
01:25:30.200 --> 01:25:32.350
Come on. just say it once. sweetie.
Come on.

1584
01:25:32.600 --> 01:25:35.592
Say "dada." Say "dada."

1585
01:25:36.640 --> 01:25:37.868
We really have to go. David.

1586
01:25:38.080 --> 01:25:40.435
No. hey. five more minutes.
please? Please?

1587
01:25:41.840 --> 01:25:43.990
We're about to eat. My mom's waiting.

1588
01:25:45.240 --> 01:25:48.277
Ella. wave goodbye to Daddy. Hmm.

1589
01:25:48.560 --> 01:25:49.754
Bye-bye. Ella.

1590
01:25:50.360 --> 01:25:52.157
Merry Christmas. I love you.

1591
01:25:54.720 --> 01:25:57.360
Hey. can you give her to your mom
so that we can talk for a minute?

1592
01:25:57.600 --> 01:25:58.600
I'm sorry. David.

1593
01:25:58.840 --> 01:26:01.070
We'll call you in a couple days. Okay?

1594
01:26:03.120 --> 01:26:04.120
Bye.

1595
01:26:13.160 --> 01:26:15.151
(MEN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

1596
01:26:21.120 --> 01:26:22.473
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

1597
01:26:25.400 --> 01:26:26.400
Hey. this is David.

1598
01:26:26.600 --> 01:26:29.273
EFRAIM: Bro. you want to hear
something totally fucked up?

1599
01:26:29.480 --> 01:26:31.198
Merry Christmas. Efraim.

1600
01:26:31.400 --> 01:26:32.469
It's Christmas?

1601
01:26:32.680 --> 01:26:33.715
That's why nobody's here.

1602
01:26:33.920 --> 01:26:36.229
I was about to fire the entire office.

1603
01:26:36.440 --> 01:26:38.112
Anyway. when I was over there.

1604
01:26:38.320 --> 01:26:40.311
I was talking to our boy. Bashkim.

1605
01:26:40.520 --> 01:26:41.589
Did you know his uncle

1606
01:26:41.840 --> 01:26:44.115
works at the Albanian defense ministry?

1607
01:26:44.320 --> 01:26:45.320
No. I didn't know that.

1608
01:26:45.560 --> 01:26:46.560
Well. he does.

1609
01:26:46.800 --> 01:26:49.519
So I said. "You know what would be
interesting to me. Bashkim?

1610
01:26:49.760 --> 01:26:54.072
"I'd be curious to know what Henry
is paying the Albanians for the AK ammo."

1611
01:26:54.280 --> 01:26:55.280
Efraim?

1612
01:26:55.520 --> 01:26:57.033
Do you know what he found out?

1613
01:26:57.240 --> 01:27:00.710
That motherfucker is paying
two and a half cents a round.

1614
01:27:00.920 --> 01:27:02.990
He's charging us a 400% markup!

1615
01:27:03.200 --> 01:27:04.997
Yeah. So what? We do the same thing.

1616
01:27:05.240 --> 01:27:06.514
Yeah. but this is our contract.

1617
01:27:06.720 --> 01:27:09.440
And we almost lost it because of him
and his Chinese fucking bullets.

1618
01:27:09.560 --> 01:27:10.560
But we didn't lose it.

1619
01:27:10.760 --> 01:27:11.829
That's not the point!

1620
01:27:12.080 --> 01:27:14.616
I want to figure out a way
to cut this cocksucker out of the deal.

1621
01:27:14.640 --> 01:27:15.868
Efraim. stop.

1622
01:27:16.120 --> 01:27:17.155
No. listen to me.

1623
01:27:17.360 --> 01:27:19.032
I'm serious. man.

1624
01:27:19.240 --> 01:27:20.468
We're making money. okay?

1625
01:27:20.680 --> 01:27:23.513
He's making money.
the whole thing is fucking working.

1626
01:27:23.720 --> 01:27:25.073
Don't mess with it.

1627
01:27:25.280 --> 01:27:27.714
I don't give a fuck. He's ripping us off!

1628
01:27:28.920 --> 01:27:29.920
Look. I'm serious. okay?

1629
01:27:30.120 --> 01:27:32.840
I'm going to be on the next flight
out of here if you pull that shit.

1630
01:27:33.200 --> 01:27:36.795
Whoa. Bro. you don't have to threaten me.

1631
01:27:37.000 --> 01:27:38.433
All right? I'm your partner.

1632
01:27:38.720 --> 01:27:40.551
Yeah. it doesn't always feel like that.

1633
01:27:41.560 --> 01:27:43.391
I found this deal. And I'm over here

1634
01:27:43.600 --> 01:27:46.160
doing all the work and you're in Miami
trying to sabotage it.

1635
01:27:46.480 --> 01:27:48.277
How am I sabotaging it?

1636
01:27:48.480 --> 01:27:51.711
By trying to fuck over Henry.
the way you fuck over everybody else.

1637
01:27:51.880 --> 01:27:53.074
(SIGHS)

1638
01:27:54.560 --> 01:27:55.709
(EXHALES)

1639
01:27:56.120 --> 01:27:59.635
You're right. Henry's our partner.

1640
01:28:01.520 --> 01:28:04.592
He's the reason we got this deal.

1641
01:28:05.400 --> 01:28:08.836
I was just looking out for us
and I took it too far.

1642
01:28:10.400 --> 01:28:12.550
Don't sweat it. bro. I'll leave it alone.

1643
01:28:12.800 --> 01:28:13.915
Thank you.

1644
01:28:14.640 --> 01:28:16.870
We can't push our luck
with this shit. man.

1645
01:28:19.040 --> 01:28:21.793
All right. I'll talk to you soon. Bye.

1646
01:28:30.040 --> 01:28:31.632
(MEN SPEAKING OTHER LANGUAGE)

1647
01:28:32.080 --> 01:28:33.229
Whoa. What the fuck? Hey.

1648
01:28:34.560 --> 01:28:35.560
Fuck! Stop.

1649
01:28:36.320 --> 01:28:37.514
(MEN GRUNTING)

1650
01:28:55.320 --> 01:28:56.435
(MUFFLED SCREAMING)

1651
01:29:18.600 --> 01:29:20.192
DAVID: Stop! I don't understand!

1652
01:29:20.440 --> 01:29:21.589
(GRUNTING)

1653
01:29:21.800 --> 01:29:23.096
(KIDNAPPER 1 SPEAKS
OTHER LANGUAGE)

1654
01:29:23.120 --> 01:29:24.235
(GUN COCKING)

1655
01:29:30.960 --> 01:29:32.951
Do you understand now?

1656
01:29:33.600 --> 01:29:35.989
Yeah. Yes.

1657
01:29:36.600 --> 01:29:39.751
Did you really think
you could cut me out of my own deal?

1658
01:29:40.120 --> 01:29:41.553
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

1659
01:29:42.680 --> 01:29:43.680
DAVID: Please.

1660
01:29:50.040 --> 01:29:51.439
(WHIMPERING)

1661
01:29:52.960 --> 01:29:54.552
(MAN SPEAKING OTHER LANGUAGE)

1662
01:30:01.880 --> 01:30:02.880
DAVID: Fuck.

1663
01:30:04.520 --> 01:30:05.520
Fuck.

1664
01:30:20.120 --> 01:30:21.320
ENVER: David. we need to talk.

1665
01:30:21.520 --> 01:30:22.794
Now's not a good time.

1666
01:30:25.360 --> 01:30:27.271
I have not been paid yet.

1667
01:30:27.520 --> 01:30:29.000
What do you mean? Like for the month?

1668
01:30:29.200 --> 01:30:30.394
Ever.

1669
01:30:30.680 --> 01:30:32.477
You haven't been paid anything?

1670
01:30:32.760 --> 01:30:35.069
Your partner doesn't return phone calls.

1671
01:30:35.320 --> 01:30:37.151
My guys need to be paid.

1672
01:30:37.360 --> 01:30:39.590
They are going to stop work.

1673
01:30:40.880 --> 01:30:42.552
David. I know the real reason

1674
01:30:42.760 --> 01:30:44.432
that you want ammunition repacked.

1675
01:30:49.040 --> 01:30:50.553
Okay. look. Enver. Listen to me.

1676
01:30:50.760 --> 01:30:53.035
I gotta fly to Miami right now.
I'll be back in a week.

1677
01:30:53.200 --> 01:30:54.200
But I promise you.

1678
01:30:54.360 --> 01:30:55.576
the first thing that
I'm going do when I land

1679
01:30:55.600 --> 01:30:57.716
is make sure
you get your money wired. okay?

1680
01:31:01.440 --> 01:31:02.440
Okay.

1681
01:31:07.640 --> 01:31:08.640
David.

1682
01:31:09.040 --> 01:31:10.189
Airport. let's go.

1683
01:31:11.880 --> 01:31:12.949
David.

1684
01:31:13.520 --> 01:31:15.715
Look. I'm late for a flight.
I'll be back next week.

1685
01:31:15.920 --> 01:31:17.956
She said her husband
didn't come home last night.

1686
01:31:19.960 --> 01:31:21.757
Okay. what do you want me to do?

1687
01:31:22.000 --> 01:31:23.399
(WOMAN SPEAKING ROMANIAN)

1688
01:31:25.880 --> 01:31:27.996
She's very worried. It is not like him.

1689
01:31:28.720 --> 01:31:30.358
Tell her I don't know her husband.

1690
01:31:30.560 --> 01:31:31.560
Who's your husband?

1691
01:31:31.840 --> 01:31:33.671
WOMAN: Bashkim.

1692
01:31:44.720 --> 01:31:47.029
DAVID: No one ever heard
from Bashkim again.

1693
01:31:47.240 --> 01:31:50.630
They never found a note.
they never found a body.

1694
01:31:51.600 --> 01:31:53.352
He just fell off the planet.

1695
01:31:57.280 --> 01:31:58.872
I was done with Albania.

1696
01:32:00.200 --> 01:32:02.111
I was never going back.

1697
01:32:12.360 --> 01:32:13.360
Hi.

1698
01:32:14.840 --> 01:32:15.840
Hey.

1699
01:32:16.680 --> 01:32:20.195
The reason I went to Albania
was to repackage Chinese ammunition

1700
01:32:20.400 --> 01:32:23.198
so we could disguise it
and sell it to the U.S. government.

1701
01:32:25.120 --> 01:32:27.156
(SIGHS) That sounds illegal.

1702
01:32:27.880 --> 01:32:29.916
It is. But I'm done.

1703
01:32:30.840 --> 01:32:33.479
I swear. no matter what happens
for the rest of my life

1704
01:32:33.680 --> 01:32:35.398
I'm never going to lie to you again.

1705
01:32:41.400 --> 01:32:42.674
Mmm-hmm.

1706
01:32:43.960 --> 01:32:45.552
I love you so much. Iz.

1707
01:32:53.360 --> 01:32:55.828
What happened to your nose?

1708
01:32:57.000 --> 01:32:59.036
I was kidnapped by Albanian gangsters.

1709
01:32:59.840 --> 01:33:02.559
- I think it's broken.
- (SIGHS) Oh. my God.

1710
01:33:05.960 --> 01:33:08.428
I think I'm going to go back
to being a massage therapist.

1711
01:33:08.800 --> 01:33:10.028
Is that okay?

1712
01:33:12.160 --> 01:33:13.593
(CHUCKLES) Yes.

1713
01:33:16.160 --> 01:33:17.832
It was always okay.

1714
01:33:33.160 --> 01:33:34.798
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

1715
01:33:41.880 --> 01:33:43.359
Hey. you're back.

1716
01:33:43.560 --> 01:33:45.357
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

1717
01:33:52.920 --> 01:33:54.035
(DOOR CLOSES)

1718
01:33:54.800 --> 01:33:55.949
Whoa!

1719
01:33:56.160 --> 01:33:58.400
Bro. what are you doing back?
What happened to your face?

1720
01:33:58.600 --> 01:34:00.696
That's everything that's been delivered
on the Afghan deal.

1721
01:34:00.720 --> 01:34:01.869
I want my cut. I'm out.

1722
01:34:03.560 --> 01:34:04.754
What are you talking about?

1723
01:34:05.200 --> 01:34:07.350
He put a fucking gun to my head. man.

1724
01:34:07.800 --> 01:34:08.869
Who. Henry?

1725
01:34:09.120 --> 01:34:10.960
You said that you were going
to leave it alone.

1726
01:34:12.600 --> 01:34:14.238
Oh. fuck.

1727
01:34:15.720 --> 01:34:17.676
I fucked up.

1728
01:34:19.040 --> 01:34:20.075
I'm done. Efraim.

1729
01:34:20.280 --> 01:34:22.271
Look. you don't have to go back.

1730
01:34:22.520 --> 01:34:23.873
I hired this new guy. Ivan.

1731
01:34:24.200 --> 01:34:25.918
- He speaks Albanian.
- I'm done.

1732
01:34:32.080 --> 01:34:34.469
What. do you think
I just got 4 million bucks laying around?

1733
01:34:34.800 --> 01:34:36.028
I've thought it through.

1734
01:34:36.240 --> 01:34:38.196
I'll take 40 cents on the dollar.

1735
01:34:44.320 --> 01:34:46.231
Yeah. I thought it through too.

1736
01:34:46.600 --> 01:34:47.749
How about this?

1737
01:34:48.160 --> 01:34:49.878
How about zero cents on the dollar?

1738
01:34:50.400 --> 01:34:53.153
Let me remind you that we have a contract.

1739
01:34:53.400 --> 01:34:54.674
Fuck your contract!

1740
01:34:55.000 --> 01:34:56.433
If I asked you to build me a house.

1741
01:34:56.600 --> 01:34:58.320
and you quit after building me
half a house.

1742
01:34:58.400 --> 01:34:59.800
you think I owe you half the money?

1743
01:34:59.920 --> 01:35:01.911
Is this a fucking joke. David?

1744
01:35:02.120 --> 01:35:04.588
You have two weeks.
Otherwise. you'll hear from my lawyer.

1745
01:35:05.280 --> 01:35:06.838
- Who. Warren?
- (DOOR OPENS)

1746
01:35:07.280 --> 01:35:09.430
Are you talking about Warren?
He's my lawyer too.

1747
01:35:09.680 --> 01:35:10.829
I introduced you to him.

1748
01:35:11.480 --> 01:35:12.913
Fucking Warren.

1749
01:35:23.440 --> 01:35:24.589
DAVID: Fuck!

1750
01:35:34.520 --> 01:35:35.794
(GRUNTS)

1751
01:35:38.800 --> 01:35:40.791
(DAVID BREATHING HEAVILY)

1752
01:35:49.200 --> 01:35:52.112
RECEPTIONIST: AEY.
How may I direct your call?

1753
01:36:15.240 --> 01:36:16.719
RALPH: We fight.

1754
01:36:18.480 --> 01:36:19.833
Fight with our families.

1755
01:36:20.080 --> 01:36:21.798
fight with our business associates.

1756
01:36:23.080 --> 01:36:25.116
Sometimes we fight with our friends.

1757
01:36:25.400 --> 01:36:26.400
If God were here.

1758
01:36:26.600 --> 01:36:27.953
we'd probably fight with Him too.

1759
01:36:28.760 --> 01:36:30.079
(CHUCKLES)

1760
01:36:31.920 --> 01:36:35.276
Efraim has a heavy heart
over what's happened.

1761
01:36:37.920 --> 01:36:41.435
No offense. Ralph. but I'm not sure
you've ever met the real Efraim.

1762
01:36:42.480 --> 01:36:44.789
He's a complicated young man.

1763
01:36:45.840 --> 01:36:47.751
But he just wants to sit down and talk.

1764
01:36:48.360 --> 01:36:49.793
Find a fair solution.

1765
01:36:51.520 --> 01:36:53.238
He's asked me to mediate.

1766
01:36:57.400 --> 01:36:59.152
Let me help you. David.

1767
01:37:01.080 --> 01:37:03.389
EFRAIM: I just don't know
if I'm ready yet.

1768
01:37:03.600 --> 01:37:04.635
All right. here he is.

1769
01:37:04.920 --> 01:37:06.751
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

1770
01:37:14.880 --> 01:37:15.995
Hey. bro.

1771
01:37:17.840 --> 01:37:19.910
Good to see you.

1772
01:37:27.480 --> 01:37:29.516
Sorry things have gotten so crazy.

1773
01:37:30.080 --> 01:37:31.718
Yeah. Me too.

1774
01:37:31.920 --> 01:37:33.558
WAITRESS: You having anything. hon?

1775
01:37:33.760 --> 01:37:35.796
I'll just have a coffee. Thanks.

1776
01:37:38.280 --> 01:37:39.952
I've thought about it a lot.

1777
01:37:42.120 --> 01:37:44.588
And I don't want you to walk away
from this empty-handed.

1778
01:37:45.640 --> 01:37:46.789
Cool.

1779
01:37:47.040 --> 01:37:49.600
So I had Warren draft up
a severance agreement.

1780
01:37:49.840 --> 01:37:51.273
And I think it's pretty fair.

1781
01:37:52.440 --> 01:37:56.399
I'm prepared to pay you 50K per year
for the next four years.

1782
01:37:58.840 --> 01:38:00.034
200 grand?

1783
01:38:02.840 --> 01:38:04.512
